<task id="001" project="agent-framework-fit-assessment-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Inventory Spaarke AI code surfaces (S1-S4 + S8 catch)</title>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <tags>assessment, inventory, spaarke-ai, read-only</tags>
    <estimate>1.5h</estimate>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-summary>Completed 2026-06-03 via parallel sub-agent (commit cb883dd9). Output: notes/01-spaarke-ai-surfaces-inventory.md (5 surfaces + 7 cross-cutting observations). Key findings: (1) Microsoft.Agents.AI package is referenced in Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj but ZERO source usage — clean evidence for "half-adopted" framing; (2) S1 SprkChat is the ONLY surface using Extensions.AI primitives; S2/S3/S4 use IOpenAiClient wrapper or OpenAI.Chat SDK directly; (3) Middleware decorates ISprkChatAgent (Spaarke interface) not IChatClient — Spaarke missed canonical chatClient.AsBuilder().Use(...).Build() idiom; (4) Two S8 surfaces discovered: SessionSummarizationService + CapabilityRouter — recommend folding into S1 perimeter for task 004; (5) GitHub Issue #6268 carried forward as RED FLAG on S1 lift-to-ChatClientAgent.</completion-summary>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>000</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Produce a structured inventory of all in-BFF Spaarke AI agent surfaces (S1 SprkChat, S2 AnalysisOrchestration + JPS, S3 Builder, S4 Background AI Jobs) and catch any unanticipated surface (S8). The output is a project-local findings table at `projects/agent-framework-fit-assessment-r1/notes/01-spaarke-ai-surfaces-inventory.md` — NOT the final assessment document. Task 006 pulls from these notes.</goal>
    <context>The assessment can only be decision-grade if it's grounded in what Spaarke actually has, not what the team thinks they have. Past patterns: SprkChatAgent.cs declares itself an "Agent Framework agent" in its doc-comment but wraps raw IChatClient — the inventory must capture this kind of nuance. Surfaces that aren't surfaced here become invisible to the per-surface decision matrix in task 004.</context>
    <constraints>
      - READ-ONLY on src/ — no .cs file modifications
      - For each surface: capture (a) primary class/service, (b) what Microsoft.* abstractions it uses by name (IChatClient, ChatClientAgent, AIFunction, AIAgent, AIFunctionFactory, ChatResponseUpdate, etc.), (c) what Spaarke-specific abstractions wrap or replace those (ChatContext, IChatContextProvider, IAiToolHandler, etc.), (d) deployment model (in-process BFF? Function? other?), (e) streaming behavior, (f) state management approach, (g) middleware composition if applicable
      - Use Grep to verify abstraction usage — do not infer from class names alone
      - For S8 catch: Grep across Services/ for any IChatClient / AIAgent / IRagService usage outside Chat/Analysis/Builder/Jobs — flag anything found
      - Output as a structured markdown file with one section per surface + a "Cross-cutting observations" section
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/agent-framework-fit-assessment-r1/SPEC.md</file>
