    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Create projects/agent-framework-fit-assessment-r1/notes/ directory if not present (mkdir)</step>
    <step>S1 SprkChat: Read SprkChatAgent.cs + SprkChatAgentFactory.cs (if exists) + the 3 middleware files + CompoundIntentDetector.cs in full. Inventory the Microsoft.Extensions.AI types used; note that it does NOT use Microsoft.Agents.AI.ChatClientAgent. Capture the UseFunctionInvocation vs raw-client split rationale</step>
    <step>S2 AnalysisOrchestration: Read AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs, IPlaybookOrchestrationService.cs, and Glob Nodes/*Executor.cs. Inventory: is this LLM-driven or deterministic? Does it use any Agent Framework type, or only JPS playbook abstractions + direct LLM calls? Capture the relationship to IAiToolHandler</step>
    <step>S3 Builder: Glob Services/Ai/Builder/ + read BuilderAgentService.cs + BuilderToolDefinitions.cs + BuilderToolExecutor.cs. Same questions as S1/S2</step>
    <step>S4 Background AI jobs: Glob Services/Jobs/ + Services/Ai/Jobs/. Identify which job handlers touch AI (call IOpenAiClient, IChatClient, IRagService). For each AI-touching handler: what Microsoft.* abstractions used? Sync or async LLM call patterns?</step>
    <step>S8 catch: Grep for IChatClient | ChatClientAgent | AIAgent | AIFunctionFactory across all of Services/ (excluding the surfaces already inventoried). Flag anything found that doesn't belong to S1-S4</step>
    <step>Cross-cutting observations: Identify patterns shared across surfaces — e.g., "all surfaces use Microsoft.Extensions.AI directly; none use Microsoft.Agents.AI"; "all middleware is per-instance via the SprkChatAgent factory, not via IChatClient.AsBuilder().Use*().Build() composition"</step>
    <step>Write notes/01-spaarke-ai-surfaces-inventory.md with sections: S1 SprkChat | S2 AnalysisOrchestration | S3 Builder | S4 Background AI Jobs | S8 Discovered surfaces | Cross-cutting observations. Each surface section captures the 7 fields from constraints. Cite file:line for every claim</step>
    <step>Commit: `docs(assessment): inventory Spaarke AI code surfaces (R1 task 001)`</step>
  </steps>
